  "title": "Updating sortBy causes RefinementList to forgets showMore state",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWhen updating a RefinmentList `sortBy` value after it has been expanded, it \"forgets\" its showMore state, and returns to showing the amount of refinements specified in `limit` and not `showMoreLimit` if it has been expanded\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Go to the repro\r\n2. Click \"show more\" and view 20 options\r\n3. Click \"sort by name\"\r\n4. Watch as it \"collapses\" to 5 options\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/nervous-shtern-pt3vk8\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nThe RefinmentList should stay expanded when `sortBy` is updated\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch-hooks-web@6.44.0\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
